The President, Salvation Church of Christ (aka Solution Ground), Pastor Dr Chidube Ezenwelu, has called on all Nigerians to humble themselves if they must access the Lord’s mercy. Pastor Ezenwelu made the declaration during the week-long programme, themed, ‘Oh Lord spare thy people’ (II Chro. 7:14). The programe began on Wednesday April 27 and would be round off on Sunday, May 1t, 2022 at 21, Moses Adebisi Street, Oshogun Bus-Stop, Alapere, Ketu, Lagos. He urged the Christian leaders to stand in the gap for the masses. He recalled that Moses and Samuel represented their people when the nation was living in sin, pleaded on their behalf for mercy, God forgave them. He emphasised that leaders must come down from their horses, pull off their garments of pride or arrogance, saying they should not forget that God put them in their positions. He noted that the essence of leadership is to serve the followers, not to abuse or trample on their rights, adding leaders must be accountable to the people.